# Tricode Digital — Workflow Skills

## nvm-run
Source nvm before any npm/node command:
```bash
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm" && [ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && . "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" && <command>
```

## build-check
Quick build validation after changes:
```bash
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm" && [ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && . "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" && npm run build 2>&1
```

## dev-server-test
Start dev server, verify HTTP 200, then kill:
```bash
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm" && [ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && . "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" && npm run dev &
sleep 3
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:3000
kill $(lsof -t -i:3000) 2>/dev/null || true
```

## new-component
When creating a new component for this project:
1. Check if it needs `'use client'` (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
2. Use brand tokens from globals.css (`text-text-primary`, `bg-bg-primary`, `accent-purple`, etc.)
3. NEVER use `text-white` or `bg-black`
4. Use `font-heading` for headings (Playfair Display), default body font is Inter
5. Use `font-mono` for tech badges (JetBrains Mono)

## section-pattern
Standard section structure:
```tsx
<section id="section-id" className="relative z-[5] py-32 bg-bg-primary">
  <div className="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
    <ScrollReveal>
      <SectionHeader eyebrow="Label" heading="Title" />
    </ScrollReveal>
    {/* Content with ScrollReveal wrappers */}
  </div>
</section>
```
